This approach defines a constructor for a parametrized test class that can accept parameters that correspond to the input values for parameterized tests.  A factory method is used to create test instances with different sets of input values (in this case, a list of version strings) &lt;br&gt;

When you run the tests, an instance of `MDServiceTest` for each input value provided by the data method is created, and the constructor will initialize `version` for each instance.

```
